Durban -  Scores of people were injured in several road crashes in and around Durban on Monday morning. Rescue Care’s Garrith Jamieson said they were called to a crash in Chatsworth where two minibus taxis collided resulting in 20 children sustaining injuries. He said the children were stabilised at the scene before being taken to hospital for further care. In another crash, near the Greyville Racecourse, a 7-year-old boy was knocked while he was on his way to school. “Advanced Life Support paramedics stabilised him at the scene before transporting him to a nearby hospital for the further care that he required,” Jamieson said. Shortly thereafter, Rescue Care attended to two taxis that had collided at the intersection of Johannes Nkosi (Alice) Street and Joseph Nduli (Russel) Street in the Durban Central Business District. “A total of six patients were stabilised on the scene before being transported to various Durban Hospitals for the further care that they required,” he said. In another crash, near Quality Street, south of Durban, two cars collided in a rear end collision. “Paramedics found that three people had sustained various injuries and were treated at the scene before being transported to a nearby hospital for further care,” Jamieson said. Daily News